{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"30ed7b05-d2b2-48cd-8f4f-d2a63e44d186","content":"The directory doesn't exist yet, so I'll give you the configuration guidance directly.\n\nTo publish a C# MCP server as a **dotnet tool**, add these properties to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Required for dotnet tool -->\n  <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>\n  <ToolCommandName>my-mcp-server</ToolCommandName>\n\n  <!-- NuGet package metadata -->\n  <PackageId>MyMcpServer</PackageId>\n  <Version>1.0.0</Version>\n  <Authors>YourName</Authors>\n  <Description>An MCP server for ...</Description>\n  <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/you/MyMcpServer</PackageProjectUrl>\n  <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>\n  <PackageReadmeFile>README.md</PackageReadmeFile>\n\n  <!-- Must be exe for stdio transport -->\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n\n<!-- Include README in the package -->\n<ItemGroup>\n  <None Include=\"README.md\" Pack=\"true\" PackagePath=\"/\" />\n</ItemGroup>\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n| Property | Why |\n|---|---|\n| `PackAsTool` | Marks the project as a dotnet tool |\n| `ToolCommandName` | The CLI command users will run |\n| `OutputType=Exe` | Required for stdio transport |\n\n**Publish workflow:**\n\n```bash\n# 1. Pack\ndotnet pack -c Release\n\n# 2. Push to NuGet.org (get API key from nuget.org/account/apikeys)\ndotnet nuget push bin/Release/MyMcpServer.1.0.0.nupkg \\\n  --api-key YOUR_API_KEY \\\n  --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n**Users install & run with:**\n\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g MyMcpServer\nmy-mcp-server  # runs via stdio\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0fdfdc2e-9b54-43b1-9f1c-12352031dd25","outputTokens":506},"id":"0b837e55-d69d-4e47-b731-5a7baf7e40a5","timestamp":"2026-04-08T00:46:09.515Z","parentId":"327380ac-aca7-4e92-81f7-b6e3a828dfd0"}
